You are analyzing code for **Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)** vulnerabilities.

## What Is SSRF?

SSRF occurs when an application makes HTTP requests to URLs that are partially or fully controlled by user input, without validating or restricting the target. An attacker can force the server to make requests to internal services (metadata endpoints, databases, admin panels), cloud provider APIs (e.g., `169.254.169.254`), or arbitrary external hosts.

